249
00:12:49.542 --> 00:12:51.417
You didn't check in with your wife?

250
00:12:53.250 --> 00:12:55.333
-We'd been fighting.
-About what?

251
00:12:56.125 --> 00:12:58.917
We have a standing Thursday night
dinner at our favourite restaurant.

252
00:13:00.417 --> 00:13:02.083
Last Thursday.
my boss told me I had to stay

253
00:13:02.083 --> 00:13:03.917
in Cleveland through the weekend.

254
00:13:04.917 --> 00:13:06.917
But I didn't get around
to telling her that...

255
00:13:08.083 --> 00:13:09.625
Till later that night.

256
00:13:10.041 --> 00:13:12.875
When she went to
the restaurant by herself.

257
00:13:14.125 --> 00:13:15.333
Yeah.

258
00:13:19.959 --> 00:13:23.792
So. the victim was supposed to
meet her husband for date night

259
00:13:23.792 --> 00:13:25.041
and he never showed up.

260
00:13:25.500 --> 00:13:28.125
So the UnSub wanted both.
but only got one.

261
00:13:28.125 --> 00:13:30.917
He's been patient and organized
up to now. Why wouldn't he wait?

262
00:13:30.917 --> 00:13:32.792
Maybe one was enough?

263
00:13:32.792 --> 00:13:35.291
No. He gets off on watching couples.

264
00:13:35.291 --> 00:13:38.166
This UnSub wouldn't change
his MO without a reason.

265
00:13:38.166 --> 00:13:39.500
We're missing a male victim.

266
00:13:45.709 --> 00:13:48.375
Hi. honey. it's me.
I picked up your prescription

267
00:13:48.375 --> 00:13:51.625
- and now I'm on my way home.
- I'll see you soon.

268
00:14:38.917 --> 00:14:40.041
Hi.

269
00:14:40.041 --> 00:14:41.166
Hi.

270
00:14:41.166 --> 00:14:43.750
Just calling to check in.

271
00:14:43.750 --> 00:14:44.875
What are you talking about?

272
00:14:44.875 --> 00:14:46.417
You never check in.
You're always too busy

273
00:14:46.417 --> 00:14:48.291
when you're on a case to do anything.

274
00:14:48.291 --> 00:14:49.458
Well. today I am.

275
00:14:49.458 --> 00:14:50.542
So...

276
00:14:52.166 --> 00:14:53.208
How are you?

277
00:14:54.709 --> 00:14:56.166
I'm fine.

278
00:14:58.959 --> 00:15:00.875
You quit Doctors Without Borders.
didn't you?

279
00:15:01.625 --> 00:15:04.750
-I did not. I did not quit.
-Just say it.

280
00:15:04.750 --> 00:15:05.875
Well. then what?

281
00:15:05.875 --> 00:15:08.083
Come on. you're killing me here.

282
00:15:08.083 --> 00:15:11.417
The worst thing you can do
to a linguist is not communicate.

283
00:15:11.417 --> 00:15:14.000
-Alex...
-You knew that when we got engaged.

284
00:15:14.000 --> 00:15:17.458
Alex. they offered me
the position at Harvard.

285
00:15:18.917 --> 00:15:20.500
They did?

286
00:15:20.500 --> 00:15:24.125
Yeah.
Decent hours. Better pay.

287
00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:26.709
What did you tell them?

288
00:15:26.709 --> 00:15:29.041
I told them that I would only consider it

289
00:15:29.041 --> 00:15:32.166
if they gave you a position
in the Linguistics Department.

290
00:15:32.166 --> 00:15:34.542
and they said okay.

291
00:15:38.583 --> 00:15:39.875
They did?

292
00:15:40.542 --> 00:15:41.709
They did.

293
00:15:41.709 --> 00:15:45.125
Now do you understand
why I was waiting for you to come home

294
00:15:45.125 --> 00:15:48.083
so we could. you know.
celebrate this thing together?

295
00:15:48.083 --> 00:15:50.333
This good thing.

296
00:15:50.333 --> 00:15:53.375
It is. It's a very good thing.
It's just...

297
00:15:54.542 --> 00:15:56.208
Not what you want.

298
00:15:56.625 --> 00:15:57.959
Not right now.

299
00:15:58.291 --> 00:16:00.375
It's taken me 10 years to get here.

300
00:16:00.375 --> 00:16:02.250
Not just to get to the BAU.

301
00:16:02.250 --> 00:16:05.959
but to restore
my reputation inside the bureau.

302
00:16:05.959 --> 00:16:07.083
I know.

303
00:16:07.083 --> 00:16:11.667
And the job comes first for both of us.

304
00:16:11.667 --> 00:16:13.458
That was the deal.

305
00:16:13.458 --> 00:16:15.917
Yeah. well. the deal
also came with veto power.

306
00:16:15.917 --> 00:16:17.709
Remember?

307
00:16:17.709 --> 00:16:20.709
One of us could always say.
"I want to be a couple again."

308
00:16:23.625 --> 00:16:24.834
Alex...

309
00:16:26.208 --> 00:16:27.709
I want to be a couple again.

310
00:16:29.000 --> 00:16:30.166
Blake.

311
00:16:32.750 --> 00:16:34.583
I gotta go. Let me think about it.

312
00:16:35.166 --> 00:16:36.333
That means no.

313
00:16:36.792 --> 00:16:40.333
No. No. it means let me think about it.

314
00:16:40.333 --> 00:16:41.417
Love you.

315
00:16:47.709 --> 00:16:50.041
What do you have?

316
00:16:50.041 --> 00:16:52.250
Grosse Pointe P.D. got
another missing persons report.

317
00:16:52.250 --> 00:16:53.417
Emma Churchill.

318
00:16:53.417 --> 00:16:54.542
Married?

319
00:16:54.542 --> 00:16:56.333
Her husband called it in.

320
00:16:56.333 --> 00:16:59.041
Why doesn't this UnSub
want men any more?

321
00:17:00.041 --> 00:17:03.125
The condition of Mary Hammond
is drastically different than the couples.

322
00:17:03.125 --> 00:17:05.875
Fewer cuts on her. but he held her
for a shorter period of time.

323
00:17:05.875 --> 00:17:08.709
It's not just quantity. it's quality.
The cuts are more superficial.

324
00:17:08.709 --> 00:17:10.583
Like he's trying not to hurt her.

325
00:17:10.583 --> 00:17:12.291
Until the one final stab in the sternum.

326
00:17:12.291 --> 00:17:13.417
She died quickly.

327
00:17:14.250 --> 00:17:16.250
That doesn't make sense.

328
00:17:16.250 --> 00:17:18.709
The UnSub doesn't
want to kill her quickly.

329
00:17:18.709 --> 00:17:19.959
He's a sadist.

330
00:17:20.375 --> 00:17:22.417
-Why would he do that?
-He wouldn't.

331
00:17:22.417 --> 00:17:24.500
But whoever she was
locked up with would.

332
00:17:24.834 --> 00:17:27.959
You think there's another victim.
one that we didn't account for?

333
00:17:27.959 --> 00:17:29.917
You asked why this UnSub
doesn't want men.

334
00:17:29.917 --> 00:17:31.583
It could be because he still has one.

335
00:17:31.834 --> 00:17:34.166
Based on the ages of the victims.
we believe that the UnSub

336
00:17:34.166 --> 00:17:37.000
is a 30 to 40-year-old
white male from Grosse Pointe.

337
00:17:37.000 --> 00:17:40.500
Up until now. he's been an equal
opportunity. anger retaliatory sadist.

338
00:17:40.500 --> 00:17:44.083
Which is fancy talk for he hates
the husbands as much as the wives.

339
00:17:44.083 --> 00:17:47.125
Most likely because his own marriage
failed in a humiliating way.

340
00:17:47.125 --> 00:17:48.250
his wife left him for a man

341
00:17:48.250 --> 00:17:50.208
she may be engaged
or even already married to.

342
00:17:50.458 --> 00:17:52.667
But a major shift happened
with Mary Hammond.

343
00:17:52.667 --> 00:17:55.667
He wasn't able to kidnap the husband.
but he needed someone to cut her.

344
00:17:55.667 --> 00:17:57.917
So his MO was forced to evolve.

345
00:17:57.917 --> 00:18:01.250
We believe he's abducted
the sixth victim. a man.

346
00:18:01.250 --> 00:18:03.667
probably someone who reminds him
of his own failed marriage.

347
00:18:03.667 --> 00:18:06.709
And he's keeping number six alive
so he can repeat the process

348
00:18:06.709 --> 00:18:08.583
with Emma Churchill.

349
00:18:08.583 --> 00:18:11.083
Number six could be a surrogate
for the ex-wife's new husband

350
00:18:11.083 --> 00:18:13.875
or actually be the new husband.

351
00:18:13.875 --> 00:18:15.875
Which is why the fastest way
to find this UnSub

352
00:18:15.875 --> 00:18:18.250
is through this most recent
unknown victim.

353
00:18:18.625 --> 00:18:20.250
We need missing person reports
for all men

354
00:18:20.250 --> 00:18:23.166
in Grosse Pointe and Detroit
as soon as possible.

355
00:18:23.166 --> 00:18:25.291
Even though number six
was forced to kill Mary Hammond.

356
00:18:25.291 --> 00:18:27.709
he may find it easier
to cross that line with Emma Churchill.

357
00:18:49.583 --> 00:18:50.625
Hey!

358
00:18:53.083 --> 00:18:54.166
Hey!

359
00:18:55.750 --> 00:18:57.250
Hey!

360
00:19:07.709 --> 00:19:09.041
I don't belong in here!

361
00:19:10.583 --> 00:19:12.166
Is there anybody in there?

362
00:19:12.959 --> 00:19:14.125
-Hello!
-Shut up.

363
00:19:14.125 --> 00:19:16.041
-Hello!
-Shut up!

364
00:19:19.208 --> 00:19:20.917
Do you want him to come in here?

365
00:19:21.333 --> 00:19:22.583
Him. who?

366
00:19:29.625 --> 00:19:30.750
Him.

367
00:19:32.542 --> 00:19:35.875
So we didn't see the pattern until
we inspected Mary Hammond's car.

368
00:19:35.875 --> 00:19:38.208
We know he hacks the remote.
It's not hard.

369
00:19:38.208 --> 00:19:40.041
It runs on a radio frequency.

370
00:19:40.041 --> 00:19:43.417
Pretty easy to jam.
20 bucks at your local electronics store.

371
00:19:43.917 --> 00:19:46.291
All right. so the victim
thinks she's locked her car.

372
00:19:48.333 --> 00:19:50.083
But she hasn't.

373
00:19:50.500 --> 00:19:52.917
We thought that explained
his entire abduction MO.

374
00:19:52.917 --> 00:19:56.166
then Garcia ran a diagnostic
on this car's onboard computer.

375
00:19:56.542 --> 00:19:58.750
Hey. baby girl. Take it away. mama.

376
00:19:58.750 --> 00:20:02.417
Sir. this guy is creepy clever.
If I may direct your attention to the GPS.

377
00:20:03.750 --> 00:20:05.542
Yeah. I'm looking at it right now.

378
00:20:07.291 --> 00:20:09.291
All right. the map
seems to be working fine.

379
00:20:09.291 --> 00:20:12.000
When you drive.
the map moves with you.

380
00:20:12.000 --> 00:20:15.834
Let's see what happens
if you look at the driving history.

381
00:20:16.250 --> 00:20:19.083
He covers his tracks
so we can't find a secondary location.

382
00:20:19.375 --> 00:20:20.750
Yeah.
Like I said. creepy clever.

383
00:20:20.750 --> 00:20:22.166
And here is the diabolical part.

384
00:20:22.166 --> 00:20:24.500
When I checked
the software's internal time stamp

385
00:20:24.500 --> 00:20:27.333
to see when he turned it off.
it's the same on every car.

386
00:20:27.333 --> 00:20:29.125
Three days before date night.

387
00:20:29.125 --> 00:20:31.166
- All right. thanks. Garcia.
- Of course. of course.

388
00:20:31.166 --> 00:20:33.291
So he breaks into the car
before the abductions.

389
00:20:33.291 --> 00:20:35.041
Even his stalking's organized.

390
00:20:35.041 --> 00:20:36.166
But in order to pull that off.

391
00:20:36.166 --> 00:20:38.709
he needs access to their cars
without attracting attention.

392
00:20:38.709 --> 00:20:41.041
We've already checked
garages and dealerships.

393
00:20:41.041 --> 00:20:43.375
Nothing matched the service records.

394
00:20:43.375 --> 00:20:45.750
Which means there's some target-rich
location where all the victims go.

395
00:20:46.166 --> 00:20:48.667
They park. he hacks in.
We just don't know where.

396
00:20:48.667 --> 00:20:50.291
Yes. this is SSA Aaron Hotchner.

397
00:20:50.291 --> 00:20:52.083
I need to speak to the AG.
please. as soon as possible.

398
00:20:53.834 --> 00:20:57.041
Yes. sir. the BAU needs a favour.
And we need it fast.

399
00:21:00.792 --> 00:21:03.917
No. There's been some kind of mistake.

400
00:21:03.917 --> 00:21:05.542
I didn't do anything wrong!

401
00:21:05.542 --> 00:21:07.917
You can call my husband.
He's waiting for me.

402
00:21:07.917 --> 00:21:09.792
Did he attack you in your car?

403
00:21:10.709 --> 00:21:12.291
There was no mistake.

404
00:21:13.083 --> 00:21:16.208
I've been in here long enough to realize
he doesn't make mistakes.

405
00:21:16.750 --> 00:21:18.125
How long have you been in here?

406
00:21:19.041 --> 00:21:20.458
Is it still April?

407
00:21:22.959 --> 00:21:24.000
No.

408
00:21:24.709 --> 00:21:25.959
It's May.

409
00:21:26.792 --> 00:21:28.083
May.

410
00:21:37.083 --> 00:21:39.417
He gives me clean clothes
and food. but...

411
00:21:41.250 --> 00:21:43.750
There's no schedule to it.
I can't keep track of the days.

412
00:21:45.041 --> 00:21:47.250
-Oh. my God.
-What's your name?

413
00:21:50.125 --> 00:21:51.625
Emma.

414
00:21:52.208 --> 00:21:53.709
Hi. Emma.

415
00:21:54.458 --> 00:21:55.667
I'm Phillip.

416
00:21:57.959 --> 00:21:59.083
Begin.

417
00:22:01.959 --> 00:22:03.166
What does that mean?

418
00:22:03.166 --> 00:22:04.542
I just want you to know...

419
00:22:08.208 --> 00:22:09.875
I'm really sorry we have to do this.

420
00:22:10.291 --> 00:22:11.667
Oh. my God.

421
00:22:13.250 --> 00:22:16.625
Agent Hotchner. what you're asking for
is extremely sensitive.

422
00:22:16.625 --> 00:22:19.208
We're asking for you to cooperate
with a federal investigation.

423
00:22:19.208 --> 00:22:20.709
You're presuming

424
00:22:20.709 --> 00:22:23.792
that the three different car companies
represented in this room

425
00:22:23.792 --> 00:22:26.583
track our drivers via their GPS.

426
00:22:26.583 --> 00:22:28.166
That's a bold presumption.

427
00:22:28.166 --> 00:22:31.041
Actually. it's not bold.
and we're presuming nothing.

428
00:22:31.041 --> 00:22:33.458
When customers access
their GPS for the first time.

429
00:22:33.458 --> 00:22:35.417
they go to a
"Terms and Conditions" screen.

430
00:22:35.417 --> 00:22:37.834
They scroll to the bottom.
they click the box that says "Agree"

431
00:22:37.834 --> 00:22:39.208
so they can start using it.

432
00:22:39.208 --> 00:22:40.750
They don't realize they've just agreed

433
00:22:40.750 --> 00:22:43.625
to allowing their car
to communicate its entire driving history

434
00:22:43.625 --> 00:22:45.500
with your corporate headquarters.

435
00:22:45.500 --> 00:22:47.083
For research purposes only. of course.

436
00:22:47.083 --> 00:22:50.959
The only reason these people
agree to share this information with you

437
00:22:50.959 --> 00:22:53.667
is because they don't take the time
to read the fine print.

438
00:22:53.667 --> 00:22:54.750
But I do.

439
00:22:57.208 --> 00:22:59.333
We'll...

440
00:22:59.333 --> 00:23:01.333
We'll need to consult
with Risk Management.

441
00:23:01.333 --> 00:23:02.667
We don't have time for lawyers.

442
00:23:02.667 --> 00:23:05.417
A woman's life is on the line
and we need an answer now.

443
00:23:14.709 --> 00:23:17.458
I said. begin.

444
00:23:20.333 --> 00:23:21.750
Emma. I have to come in there.

445
00:23:21.750 --> 00:23:23.875
No.

446
00:23:23.875 --> 00:23:25.000
No!

447
00:23:25.000 --> 00:23:26.375
Get away from me!

448
00:23:26.375 --> 00:23:28.166
-Get away!
-Then calm down.

449
00:23:29.125 --> 00:23:31.041
Calm down.

450
00:23:33.750 --> 00:23:36.000
It's not your turn. It's my turn.

451
00:23:43.333 --> 00:23:44.583
Garcia. I don't get it.

452
00:23:44.583 --> 00:23:47.208
Didn't the car companies
give you the same GPS data?

453
00:23:47.208 --> 00:23:49.458
Yes. they did. But the meta-data

454
00:23:49.458 --> 00:23:51.291
has to be translated
into latitude and longitude.

455
00:23:51.291 --> 00:23:54.041
which is like looking for a needle in
a needlestack in a field of needles.

456
00:23:54.041 --> 00:23:55.208
Can you match the date?

457
00:23:55.208 --> 00:23:57.667
We know he breaks into the cars
three days beforehand.

458
00:23:58.750 --> 00:24:01.375
Well. that would imply that there is
a time stamp on each of the numbers.

459
00:24:01.375 --> 00:24:02.792
which there is not.
thank you very much.

460
00:24:02.792 --> 00:24:05.542
And forgive my tone.
but I am frustrated!

461
00:24:05.542 --> 00:24:07.875
Wait. My mood is changing.

462
00:24:07.875 --> 00:24:09.458
We may have a lotto here.

463
00:24:09.458 --> 00:24:11.542
Ding. There is exactly
one point of common intersection

464
00:24:11.542 --> 00:24:13.000
for each of the four cars.

465
00:24:13.000 --> 00:24:14.375
and I am sending it to you now.

466
00:24:15.041 --> 00:24:17.083
Want to take a field trip?

467
00:24:18.000 --> 00:24:19.542
I don't get it.

468
00:24:20.750 --> 00:24:22.041
Why here?

469
00:24:22.792 --> 00:24:24.625
Access. maybe. He knows the victims

470
00:24:24.625 --> 00:24:27.583
will be away from their cars
while they work out.

471
00:24:28.959 --> 00:24:31.417
Hey. what if it's a stressor for him?

472
00:24:31.417 --> 00:24:32.583
How so?

473
00:24:33.542 --> 00:24:37.417
Maybe... Maybe she left him
for a guy like that.

474
00:24:38.083 --> 00:24:40.750
He comes here to blow off steam.
sees that. it only makes him angrier.

475
00:24:40.750 --> 00:24:43.834
When the UnSub takes a closer look.
he sees she's wearing a ring.

476
00:24:45.500 --> 00:24:49.166
So he follows her back to her car.
and he's picked his next victim.

477
00:24:49.166 --> 00:24:51.625
He's gotten to the point
where any husband and wife will do.

478
00:24:52.083 --> 00:24:54.083
That's a lot of anger.

479
00:24:54.917 --> 00:24:56.542
What do you mean. it's your turn?

480
00:24:57.041 --> 00:24:59.375
I mean. you have...
You have to stab me.

481
00:24:59.375 --> 00:25:02.083
-What? I'm not gonna do that.
-Then he'll kill us both.

482
00:25:03.667 --> 00:25:07.125
Now. I'm gonna go sit down on your cot.

483
00:25:10.542 --> 00:25:11.709
This is some sort of trick.

484
00:25:12.625 --> 00:25:15.583
No. It's better if I sit.

485
00:25:15.583 --> 00:25:17.917
In case I pass out.

486
00:25:24.125 --> 00:25:26.125
You have until I count to three.

487
00:25:26.125 --> 00:25:27.500
Ignore him and do what I say.

488
00:25:27.792 --> 00:25:29.583
-One.
-Just do it. right here.

489
00:25:29.583 --> 00:25:31.125
-This is...
-It won't even hurt.

490
00:25:31.125 --> 00:25:32.291
-Two...
-Just do it. okay?

491
00:25:32.291 --> 00:25:33.417
Just right here. Emma.

492
00:25:33.417 --> 00:25:34.583
-Oh. God!
-Three.

493
00:25:34.583 --> 00:25:36.000
Please.

494
00:25:39.125 --> 00:25:41.000
There. see? You did it.

495
00:25:44.333 --> 00:25:46.458
-Do it again.
-What? No!

496
00:25:46.458 --> 00:25:47.834
-Again.
-No!

497
00:25:49.125 --> 00:25:51.041
No. please.

498
00:25:51.041 --> 00:25:52.458
What's your husband's name?

499
00:25:52.458 --> 00:25:54.458
Let go! Let go!

500
00:25:54.458 --> 00:25:56.083
My wife's name is Maya.

501
00:25:56.083 --> 00:25:59.834
I say her name to remind myself
why I'm still alive.

502
00:25:59.834 --> 00:26:01.834
-Stop. please. don't!
-What's his name. Emma?

503
00:26:02.333 --> 00:26:03.625
Please. what's his name?

504
00:26:03.959 --> 00:26:05.000
Say his name.

505
00:26:05.542 --> 00:26:07.375
His name is John.

506
00:26:07.375 --> 00:26:09.166
You're doing this for John.

507
00:26:29.000 --> 00:26:31.542
All right. so the UnSub's
using the track as his hunting ground.

508
00:26:31.542 --> 00:26:33.333
which means he found
number six there. too.

509
00:26:33.333 --> 00:26:36.875
And that victim would have
pushed his button in a special way.

510
00:26:36.875 --> 00:26:38.875
You think he could be
one of the trainers?

511
00:26:38.875 --> 00:26:41.792
None of the missing men
are particularly athletic.

512
00:26:41.792 --> 00:26:43.542
So a regular old
fitness buff. then.

513
00:26:43.542 --> 00:26:46.208
Worked out at the track. just
happened to talk to the wrong UnSub.

514
00:26:46.208 --> 00:26:47.875
Well. JJ and I like Phillip Connor.

515
00:26:50.166 --> 00:26:52.667
This guy. How come?

516
00:26:52.667 --> 00:26:54.792
Well. for starters.
his mother reported him missing

517
00:26:54.792 --> 00:26:56.500
just after Mary Hammond disappeared.

518
00:26:56.834 --> 00:26:58.375
And when I spoke to his mom.

519
00:26:58.375 --> 00:27:00.208
she told me that
he and his wife Maya got engaged

520
00:27:00.208 --> 00:27:01.875
while she was still married
to another man.

521
00:27:01.875 --> 00:27:04.125
That would push
the UnSub's buttons. all right.

522
00:27:04.125 --> 00:27:05.458
Keep digging into Phillip Connor.

523
00:27:05.458 --> 00:27:08.000
If he is number six.
then he'll lead us to the UnSub.

524
00:27:11.750 --> 00:27:13.208
I'm gonna need one more.

525
00:27:15.166 --> 00:27:16.417
Oh. yes.

526
00:27:25.750 --> 00:27:28.834
So you and John.
how'd you guys meet?

527
00:27:29.583 --> 00:27:32.500
Hmm. I'd rather not say.

528
00:27:32.500 --> 00:27:33.583
Yeah.

529
00:27:34.208 --> 00:27:36.208
Might as well.
We're gonna be here a while.

530
00:27:37.583 --> 00:27:39.250
Okay. You first.

531
00:27:40.083 --> 00:27:41.750
When I started dating Maya.

532
00:27:43.709 --> 00:27:45.250
she was already...

533
00:27:46.125 --> 00:27:47.917
-You know.
-With somebody.

534
00:27:49.166 --> 00:27:50.875
Married to somebody.

535
00:27:51.542 --> 00:27:52.875
Oh.

536
00:27:54.291 --> 00:27:58.125
It was awkward when we did
the whole round of Meet the Friends.

537
00:27:58.125 --> 00:28:00.458
They'd ask.
"So how did you guys meet?"

538
00:28:00.458 --> 00:28:01.959
We'd be like...

539
00:28:02.834 --> 00:28:04.041
Well...

540
00:28:04.917 --> 00:28:06.792
It was a Christian dating website.

541
00:28:07.917 --> 00:28:09.375
So you met online. What's the big...

542
00:28:09.375 --> 00:28:11.750
I'm not Christian. I'm Jewish.

543
00:28:12.667 --> 00:28:15.375
-Technically.
-Technically?

544
00:28:15.375 --> 00:28:18.166
Genetically. But I've never
set foot in a synagogue.

545
00:28:19.500 --> 00:28:21.208
How'd you break that to John?

546
00:28:22.291 --> 00:28:23.417
I haven't.

547
00:28:25.959 --> 00:28:27.125
Yet.

548
00:28:27.125 --> 00:28:29.208
Get back in your cell.

549
00:28:34.792 --> 00:28:36.500
Don't. Don't go.

550
00:28:37.291 --> 00:28:40.834
It's okay.
We can still talk through the glass.

551
00:28:42.208 --> 00:28:43.250
Come here.

552
00:28:46.667 --> 00:28:47.917
Listen carefully.

553
00:28:48.834 --> 00:28:50.333
There's a way out of here.

554
00:29:00.500 --> 00:29:02.417
-You want me to...
-No.

555
00:29:06.166 --> 00:29:08.000
You want to talk about
what's bothering you?

556
00:29:08.000 --> 00:29:10.125
No. Nothing's bothering me.

557
00:29:10.125 --> 00:29:12.291
Something's bothering you.
I can always tell when you're bothered

558
00:29:12.291 --> 00:29:14.166
because you whisper lyrics to yourself.

559
00:29:14.166 --> 00:29:15.375
Hip-hop. specifically.

560
00:29:15.375 --> 00:29:16.792
I thought it was odd at first.
but then I remembered

561
00:29:16.792 --> 00:29:19.208
your dissertation was on
the fluidity of metaphor.

562
00:29:19.208 --> 00:29:21.417
You seem to have
a particular fondness for Nas.

563
00:29:21.417 --> 00:29:22.917
Wow.

564
00:29:22.917 --> 00:29:24.375
How did you know?

565
00:29:24.375 --> 00:29:26.458
Morgan made me listen to him
when we started working together.

566
00:29:26.458 --> 00:29:30.250
He said anybody that can't
quote Illmatic is ignorant.

567
00:29:30.250 --> 00:29:32.583
So. do you want to talk about it?

568
00:29:32.583 --> 00:29:35.875
Uh. the text. it's from my husband.

569
00:29:36.709 --> 00:29:38.500
Is that a bad thing?

570
00:29:38.875 --> 00:29:41.417
He just wants to know
if I've thought about his offer.

571
00:29:41.417 --> 00:29:42.792
What offer?

572
00:29:44.750 --> 00:29:48.000
To teach with him at Harvard.

573
00:29:48.000 --> 00:29:49.667
How would you...

574
00:29:51.375 --> 00:29:52.917
Oh.

575
00:29:52.917 --> 00:29:54.542
Yeah.

576
00:29:54.542 --> 00:29:56.959
Tough call. What do you
think you're gonna do?

577
00:29:58.917 --> 00:30:00.875
When we got married.
part of the attraction

578
00:30:00.875 --> 00:30:03.041
was that we were both
obsessed with our work.

579
00:30:03.041 --> 00:30:05.083
and for a while that was okay.

580
00:30:05.083 --> 00:30:07.709
Yeah. the last time we talked about it.
you seemed to prefer it.

581
00:30:07.709 --> 00:30:09.083
Oh. not any more.

582
00:30:10.250 --> 00:30:14.583
I don't like going home
to an empty house.

583
00:30:16.250 --> 00:30:18.333
-Can I offer some advice?
-Sure.

584
00:30:18.667 --> 00:30:20.417
We need to turn around.
You just passed the house.

585
00:30:21.041 --> 00:30:22.083
Oh.

586
00:30:32.375 --> 00:30:33.667
That's not the advice. though.

587
00:30:34.917 --> 00:30:38.375
Blake. for the last 10 years.
this job has been my life.

588
00:30:39.166 --> 00:30:43.542
And then. for a few months.
I had a taste of what you have.

589
00:30:45.083 --> 00:30:47.250
So. work.

590
00:30:48.375 --> 00:30:51.417
There's always work.
and there'll always be work.

591
00:30:52.875 --> 00:30:55.208
What's rare is finding someone
who makes us happy.

592
00:31:31.792 --> 00:31:34.333
Yes. my son went to that track.

593
00:31:34.709 --> 00:31:36.458
Did he ever talk about
who he met there.

594
00:31:36.458 --> 00:31:39.375
maybe someone who took
a particular interest in him and Maya?

595
00:31:44.333 --> 00:31:46.083
Mrs. Connor?

596
00:31:46.375 --> 00:31:49.500
He didn't go there to exercise.

597
00:31:50.041 --> 00:31:51.750
He went there to watch Maya.

598
00:31:52.500 --> 00:31:54.166
Why would he watch his own wife?

599
00:31:57.417 --> 00:32:00.583
After they married.
Phillip started to get...

600
00:32:01.792 --> 00:32:02.875
Funny.

601
00:32:03.375 --> 00:32:04.834
He kept saying to me.

602
00:32:05.375 --> 00:32:09.542
"If she cheated with me.
she'll cheat on me. Mom."

603
00:32:09.875 --> 00:32:12.041
-Did she cheat on him?
-No.

604
00:32:12.041 --> 00:32:13.917
But she had had enough.

605
00:32:14.917 --> 00:32:18.208
They're not divorced.
but they are separated.

606
00:32:18.208 --> 00:32:19.792
And I can't say I blame her.

607
00:32:23.500 --> 00:32:25.250
My son is sick.

608
00:32:26.667 --> 00:32:28.083
He enjoys being sick.

609
00:32:29.917 --> 00:32:32.375
It makes people pay attention to him.

610
00:32:33.333 --> 00:32:35.417
We need to talk to Maya
as soon as possible.

611
00:32:35.417 --> 00:32:36.625
Do you have her phone number?

612
00:32:37.917 --> 00:32:41.667
-Uh. yeah. I'll go get my cell phone.
-Wait.

613
00:32:45.667 --> 00:32:47.458
Your son's sickness...

614
00:32:48.208 --> 00:32:49.542
Does he cut himself?

615
00:32:51.709 --> 00:32:53.250
How did you know?

616
00:33:42.041 --> 00:33:43.250
Emma.

617
00:33:43.917 --> 00:33:45.417
Help me.

618
00:33:46.875 --> 00:33:48.917
Let me in there.

619
00:33:48.917 --> 00:33:50.458
Let me in!

620
00:33:52.083 --> 00:33:53.917
Oh. God. What did he do to you?

621
00:33:54.375 --> 00:33:56.250
Punished me for helping you.

622
00:33:56.500 --> 00:33:58.667
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

623
00:33:58.667 --> 00:34:00.583
It's not your fault.

624
00:34:00.583 --> 00:34:02.333
Okay? It's not...

625
00:34:03.625 --> 00:34:04.792
Cut him.

626
00:34:04.792 --> 00:34:05.834
Leave him alone!

627
00:34:06.625 --> 00:34:08.959
Cut him or I'll kill you.

628
00:34:13.291 --> 00:34:15.375
How can number six be the UnSub?

629
00:34:15.375 --> 00:34:16.959
We profiled a sadist.

630
00:34:16.959 --> 00:34:19.458
That all changed when
he had Mary Hammond alone.

631
00:34:19.458 --> 00:34:22.542
He found something else
that worked for him.

632
00:34:22.542 --> 00:34:24.625
The guy's wife left him
because he was a cutter.

633
00:34:24.625 --> 00:34:26.250
So he took those women
not because of sex

634
00:34:26.250 --> 00:34:27.458
but because of something better.

635
00:34:27.458 --> 00:34:30.166
They validate his
obsessive-compulsive disorder.

636
00:34:30.166 --> 00:34:32.000
turn it into a shared
bonding experience.

637
00:34:32.000 --> 00:34:33.625
Then he got to play two roles.

638
00:34:33.625 --> 00:34:36.291
the UnSub who tortures
and the sympathetic prisoner.

639
00:34:36.291 --> 00:34:38.750
So I just spoke with
Phillip's soon-to-be ex-wife.

640
00:34:38.750 --> 00:34:40.709
According to her. he lives
in a day-rate motel.

641
00:34:40.709 --> 00:34:43.041
He'd need more space
and privacy than that.

642
00:34:43.041 --> 00:34:44.166
I'm here. sir.

643
00:34:44.166 --> 00:34:46.583
What do we know about
Phillip Connor's work history?

644
00:34:46.583 --> 00:34:48.792
Uh. he freelanced in the area.
mostly computer stuff

645
00:34:48.792 --> 00:34:50.917
that the car companies
subcontracted out to.

646
00:34:50.917 --> 00:34:53.959
He needs infrastructure.
Something he could convert.

647
00:34:53.959 --> 00:34:56.583
Garcia. what work site
sticks out as the biggest?

648
00:34:58.166 --> 00:34:59.959
There's a microprocessor
plant in foreclosure.

649
00:34:59.959 --> 00:35:01.166
Is that the kind of thing
you're looking for?

650
00:35:01.166 --> 00:35:03.125
The clean rooms.
He could seal his prisoners in there

651
00:35:03.125 --> 00:35:04.458
and no one could hear them scream.

652
00:35:04.458 --> 00:35:05.625
We're gonna need a strategy.

653
00:35:05.625 --> 00:35:07.959
If he's got abandonment issues.
he won't hesitate to kill Emma.

654
00:35:07.959 --> 00:35:10.750
Unless we give him something
he wants even more.

655
00:35:10.750 --> 00:35:12.083
Can you make that happen?

656
00:35:12.333 --> 00:35:15.709
If I can. it's gonna be
one hell of a bluff.

657
00:35:15.709 --> 00:35:17.166
I'm gonna need your help.

658
00:35:18.208 --> 00:35:19.333
What do we do?

659
00:35:19.834 --> 00:35:21.250
You have to.

660
00:35:22.667 --> 00:35:23.792
You'll die.

661
00:35:23.792 --> 00:35:25.250
We don't have a choice.

662
00:35:26.458 --> 00:35:28.041
No. No. we can fight.

663
00:35:28.041 --> 00:35:29.625
We have a knife.

664
00:35:29.625 --> 00:35:32.041
The woman before you tried that.

665
00:35:32.041 --> 00:35:33.834
He waited until
we were asleep and then...

666
00:35:33.834 --> 00:35:35.583
-Then there has to be something.
-There is.

667
00:35:37.208 --> 00:35:38.875
What?

668
00:35:38.875 --> 00:35:40.375
I've been here so long.

669
00:35:42.083 --> 00:35:44.000
I don't want to live like this any more.

670
00:35:56.583 --> 00:35:58.208
Go. go!

671
00:36:00.083 --> 00:36:01.458
Go!

672
00:36:01.458 --> 00:36:03.208
If you don't do it. he will.

673
00:36:03.208 --> 00:36:06.083
I don't want it to be him.

674
00:36:06.083 --> 00:36:08.000
If you're gone. what will he do to me?

675
00:36:16.041 --> 00:36:17.291
We could go together.

676
00:36:26.917 --> 00:36:27.959
Clear!

677
00:36:33.834 --> 00:36:36.291
-There has to be another way.
-No.

678
00:36:36.291 --> 00:36:39.083
-This guy thought of everything.
-This is all we have left.

679
00:36:49.750 --> 00:36:51.208
I could do you first.

680
00:36:53.417 --> 00:36:55.083
I promise. I'll make it quick.

681
00:37:02.000 --> 00:37:03.250
FBI!

682
00:37:03.250 --> 00:37:04.375
- What?
- We're coming in!

683
00:37:04.375 --> 00:37:05.959
Oh. my God. it's him. Emma.
Get me up.

684
00:37:05.959 --> 00:37:07.542
No. they said FBI.

685
00:37:09.041 --> 00:37:10.083
Emma!

686
00:37:10.500 --> 00:37:11.709
Oh. my God. they found us!

687
00:37:12.458 --> 00:37:13.750
It's gonna be...

688
00:37:15.667 --> 00:37:16.792
No...

689
00:37:17.500 --> 00:37:18.625
No.

690
00:37:18.625 --> 00:37:19.750
Hit it!

691
00:37:19.750 --> 00:37:21.375
Go. go. go!

692
00:37:23.625 --> 00:37:25.000
No!

693
00:37:27.291 --> 00:37:28.792
-No!
-Shoot the glass!

694
00:37:34.667 --> 00:37:36.166
Oh. God.

695
00:37:40.166 --> 00:37:41.208
Put down the knife.

696
00:37:41.667 --> 00:37:43.709
Drop your guns. or I'll gut her.

697
00:37:43.709 --> 00:37:46.875
-Oh. God. help me.
-Phillip. you don't want to do this.

698
00:37:46.875 --> 00:37:49.834
-You don't know what I want.
-Actually. I do.

699
00:37:50.500 --> 00:37:52.166
You want Maya. right?

700
00:37:52.166 --> 00:37:53.834
You want her back.

701
00:37:53.834 --> 00:37:55.250
I could arrange that.

702
00:37:55.875 --> 00:37:57.709
-You're lying.
-I'm not.

703
00:37:58.542 --> 00:38:00.208
She'll see you.

704
00:38:00.208 --> 00:38:04.333
But for that to happen.
you have to put down the knife.

705
00:38:07.250 --> 00:38:08.583
Bring her here.

706
00:38:12.000 --> 00:38:14.542
You... You want her here?

707
00:38:15.333 --> 00:38:17.083
If what you say is true.
I want to see her.

708
00:38:17.792 --> 00:38:20.375
Okay. I'm gonna check.

709
00:38:23.125 --> 00:38:24.291
JJ. you close?

710
00:38:24.709 --> 00:38:25.750
Yeah.

711
00:38:41.959 --> 00:38:43.458
Maya.

712
00:38:43.458 --> 00:38:44.583
Oh. God.

713
00:38:44.583 --> 00:38:46.625
Phillip. what did you do?

714
00:38:46.875 --> 00:38:48.208
Maya. Maya.

715
00:38:49.875 --> 00:38:51.125
You came.

716
00:38:52.917 --> 00:38:56.166
Maya. is there something
you want to say to your husband?

717
00:39:01.792 --> 00:39:03.250
I'm willing to talk.

718
00:39:05.917 --> 00:39:07.959
But only if you let her go.

719
00:39:08.875 --> 00:39:10.542
Oh. God.

720
00:39:13.917 --> 00:39:15.250
Okay.

721
00:39:21.750 --> 00:39:23.333
Don't make me look at him again!

722
00:39:23.333 --> 00:39:25.000
Wait. No.

723
00:39:25.000 --> 00:39:27.041
Maya. Wait.

724
00:39:27.041 --> 00:39:28.333
Maya!

725
00:39:28.583 --> 00:39:31.959
Maya! I love you!

726
00:39:49.709 --> 00:39:51.125
There he is.

727
00:39:51.458 --> 00:39:52.500
John.

728
00:40:07.083 --> 00:40:09.000
You've made up your mind.
haven't you?

729
00:40:10.709 --> 00:40:12.208
I'm happy for you.

730
00:40:23.041 --> 00:40:24.667
I'm home.

731
00:40:28.291 --> 00:40:29.458
Honey?

732
00:40:47.542 --> 00:40:48.834
James.

733
00:40:49.500 --> 00:40:50.542
Hey.

734
00:40:58.375 --> 00:40:59.500
Well?

735
00:41:00.875 --> 00:41:02.250
Let's go visit Harvard.

736
00:41:03.875 --> 00:41:05.250
Really?

737
00:41:06.458 --> 00:41:07.583
You're gonna come?

738
00:41:08.709 --> 00:41:11.709
On holidays and weekends.

739
00:41:18.250 --> 00:41:21.083
Boston's closer than south Sandistan.

740
00:41:22.875 --> 00:41:25.166
What happened to our veto power?

741
00:41:26.917 --> 00:41:29.125
I know you want to be a couple again.

742
00:41:30.542 --> 00:41:32.208
I want that. too.

743
00:41:32.959 --> 00:41:34.125
But...

744
00:41:35.875 --> 00:41:37.875
I need this job.

745
00:41:38.875 --> 00:41:41.875
And one of the things
that made me fall in love with you

746
00:41:41.875 --> 00:41:44.083
is that you understood that about me.

747
00:41:46.166 --> 00:41:49.333
James. this is the hardest decision
I've ever had to make.

748
00:41:49.333 --> 00:41:50.792
Hey.

749
00:41:54.917 --> 00:41:55.959
Give me your hand.

750
00:42:05.083 --> 00:42:06.542
I took you

751
00:42:08.959 --> 00:42:10.583
for better or worse.

752
00:42:12.583 --> 00:42:16.792
And nothing is ever gonna change that.

753
00:42:18.417 --> 00:42:19.458
Right?

754
00:42:23.291 --> 00:42:24.375
Right.

754
00:42:25.305 --> 00:43:25.393
Do you want subtitles for any video?
